Source: softether-vpn
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Andrej Shadura <andrewsh@debian.org>
Build-Depends:
 debhelper-compat (= 12),
 cmake,
 libncurses5-dev,
 libreadline-dev,
 libssl-dev,
 zlib1g-dev,
Standards-Version: 4.5.0
Homepage: https://www.softether.org/
Vcs-Browser: https://salsa.debian.org/debian/softether-vpn
Vcs-Git: https://salsa.debian.org/debian/softether-vpn.git

Package: softether-vpnserver
Architecture: any
Depends:
 softether-common,
 softether-vpncmd,
 ${misc:Depends},
 ${shlibs:Depends}
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Description: multiprotocol VPN program (server daemon)
 SoftEther is an open-source cross-platform multi-protocol VPN program.
 .
 SoftEther supports:
 .
  * SSL-VPN, OpenVPN, IPsec, L2TP, MS-SSTP, L2TPv3, EtherIP
  * VPN over ICMP and VPN over DNS
  * Ethernet-bridging (L2) and IP-routing (L3) over VPN
  * Embedded dynamic DNS and NAT traversal
  * AES 256-bit and RSA 4096-bit encryption
  * RADIUS and NT domain user authentication
  * X.509 client certificates
  * Packet logging
  * Web GUI
 .
 This package ships the VPN server daemon.

